AssignedTask.Name: Troubled Lands
AssignedTask.Description: This area of the barony is said to be a breeding ground for bandits, brawlers and cutthroats. Perhaps one of your advisors should set aside these rumors, and assure the people that the guard is able to protect them.

ActiveTasks.Name: Pillage the Temple of the Elk
ActiveTasks.Description: Plunder the Temple of the Elk and rob it of all remaining treasure. +150 BP. Prevents future restoration of the Temple.

ActiveTasks.Name: Trade Agreement with Surtova
ActiveTasks.Description: Our merchants will receive the right to establish a sizeable trading post in the heart of New Stetven. Each city in the barony gains an extra +5 BP per week; +2 BP for each Town; and +1 BP for each village.

ActiveTasks.Name: Rebuild the Temple of the Elk
ActiveTasks.Description: Restore the Temple of the Elk to its former glory, making it the center for Erastil's worship in all the surrounding areas. Unlocks a special region upgrade. Prevents pillaging the Temple.

ActiveTasks.Name: Ezvanki's Offer
ActiveTasks.Description: Ezvanki Keegh, High Priest of Erastil from Restov, has a strong interest in spreading the Stag God's faith across the region. He is eager to build a shrine dedicated to Erastil on your lands – but at his own expense. Accept his offer if you wish to gain a useful ally and a place of worship for Erastil.

ActiveTasks.Name: Research into the Nature of Curses: Davik Nettle
ActiveTasks.Description: Now that the undead engineer's curse has been lifted, it might be prudent to study it and be more prepared next time.

ActiveTasks.Name: Research into the Nature of Curses: Tartuk
ActiveTasks.Description: Tartuccio's transformation into the kobold shaman Tartuk was truly remarkable. Could it have been the result of a curse?

ActiveTasks.Name: Tristian's Training
ActiveTasks.Description: Intensive training and expeditions into the wilderness improve your companion's proficiency. This increases your companion's level, making them suitable to join your current party.

ActiveTasks.Name: Support the Regent's Endeavors
ActiveTasks.Description: Spend two weeks resolving population problems in the barony.

ActiveTasks.Name: Support the General's Endeavors
ActiveTasks.Description: Spend two weeks resolving the barony's military difficulties.

ActiveTasks.Name: Research into the Nature of Curses: the Scythe Tree
ActiveTasks.Description: The Scythe Tree came about as the result of a curse. Perhaps by studying what's left of it we might learn something...

ActiveTasks.Name: Trade Agreement with Pitax
ActiveTasks.Description: Pitax will allow our merchants to pay significantly lower trade tariffs. +4 BP per week.

ActiveTasks.Name: Research into the Nature of Curses: Jenna Tannersen
ActiveTasks.Description: Could a mother have cursed her own child? Even unwittingly?

ActiveTasks.Name: Love of the Folk
ActiveTasks.Description: The cost of buildings with a static Loyalty bonus (Alchemist, Bardic College, City Hall, Everflowing Spring, Exotic Garden, Herbalist, Magic Shop, Monument, Park, Swordlords' Academy, Temple of Cayden Cailean, Town Hall) is reduced by 10%.

ActiveTasks.Name: Claim the Kamelands
ActiveTasks.Description: Declare the Kamelands a part of your kingdom.

ActiveTasks.Name: Support the High Priest's Endeavors
ActiveTasks.Description: Spend two weeks resolving religious problems in the barony.

ActiveTasks.Name: Support the Councilor's Endeavors
ActiveTasks.Description: Spend two weeks resolving the loyalty of citizens in the barony.

ActiveTasks.Name: Proposal for Cooperation
ActiveTasks.Description: Three merchants from Absalom arrived in the region. They're ready to do business with the barony, if their conditions are met.
